      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drain the butter beans, reserving a splash of their liquid. Add the leftovers of the Bolognese ragù to a small baking dish and stir through the beans. Loosen with a bit of the reserved liquid if it looks too thick."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Melt the butter in a saucepan over a medium heat. Stir in the flour and cook for 3-4 mins until it smells nutty and starts to bubble. Gradually whisk in the milk until smooth. Simmer for 4-5 mins, stirring, until thickened. Stir in half the mustard and half the cheddar. Season with salt and loads of black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
